title: [ICE]: `Broken MIR: generator contains type [&std::option::Option<StructB>] in MIR, but typeck only knows about {ResumeTy, StructB, Option<StructB>, &StructB, impl Future<Output = StructA>, ()} and []`

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: E-needs-test
labels.description: Call for participation: writing correctness tests

labels.name: regression-from-stable-to-nightly
labels.description: Performance or correctness regression from stable to nightly.

labels.name: T-compiler

body:
### Code

```Rust
fn main() {}

struct StructA {}
struct StructB {}

impl StructA {
    fn fn_taking_struct_b(&self, struct_b: &StructB) -> bool {
        true
    }
}

async fn get_struct_a_async() -> StructA {
    StructA {}
}

async fn ice() {
    match Some(StructB {}) {
        Some(struct_b) if get_struct_a_async().await.fn_taking_struct_b(&struct_b) => {}
        _ => {}
    }
}
```


### Affected release channels

- [ ] Previous Stable
- [ ] Current Stable
- [ ] Current Beta
- [X] Current Nightly

### Rust Version

```Shell
works with rustc 1.69.0-nightly (ef982929c 2023-01-27)
but crashes with rustc 1.69.0-nightly (d8da51366 2023-01-28)
```
